        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 2:17PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 217 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Manchester, or 11 miles
north of Talbotton. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Manchester, Sprewell Bluff State Park, Flint Hill, and Woodland.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
